, and alternative media. The book will introduce students and scholars to important qualitative approaches to the study of social activism within these four research sites, which is based entirely on successful research projects that have been conducted and published in recent years. Ultimately, this book will prove integral to any students and scholars who wish to use qualitative methods for their research endeavors concerning socialactivism in contemporary society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aPolitical participation. 0aSocial action. 0aSocial change. 0aSocial movements. 4aCommunications. 4aSociology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Methodology.2bisacsh  aactivism.  aactivist networks.  aactivist organizations.  aalternative media.  aprotest.  aqualitative methods.  asocial movement.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311072901640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823274161zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823274161423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823274161/original  a978-3-11-072901-6  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK